<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[699,1227,219,515]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
COMMENTS: Although the names 
<emphasis box="[1082,1179,281,302]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">himalaya</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[699,822,308,329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">himalayana</emphasis>
(the latter overlooked in my 1999 treatment) as Latinized epithets are 
<emphasis box="[1087,1226,334,355]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">nomina nuda</emphasis>
and therefore unavailable, it has not stopped them from being used frequently in the literature (e.g., Hepburn et al., 2001). A validly proposed name is available for this race, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="1999" box="[1014,1221,441,462]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cerana" subSpecies="skorikovi">
<emphasis box="[1014,1221,441,462]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. cerana skorikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and should be used to the exclusion of other subspecific epithets.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
